---

WHAT YOU CAN DO

You are free to:
- Download, install, and use SENTINEL on your own systems
- Run SENTINEL in production on platforms generating under $100,000 USD annual
  revenue
- Read, study, and modify the source code
- Use SENTINEL for non-commercial purposes without any restrictions
- Deploy SENTINEL internally within your organization

---

WHAT YOU CANNOT DO WITHOUT PERMISSION

You may NOT:
- Offer SENTINEL as a hosted service, SaaS product, or managed service to third
  parties (whether free or paid) unless you have a written commercial license
  agreement with Sentinel Foundation
- Sublicense, resell, or transfer your rights under this license to anyone else
- Redistribute modified versions under different terms or licenses
- Remove or alter copyright notices and attribution in the code
- Use commercial derivatives of SENTINEL above the $100,000 revenue threshold
  without a separate commercial license
- Create shell entities or affiliated companies to circumvent the revenue
  threshold
- Use SENTINEL to build competing child-safety moderation platforms for
  commercial sale above the revenue threshold

---

REVENUE THRESHOLD TERMS

"Annual revenue" means all gross revenue received by your organization in the
past 12 months, calculated on a worldwide basis and including:
- Your direct business revenue
- Revenue from all subsidiaries (>50% owned)
- Revenue from all parent companies
- Revenue from all affiliated entities under common control
- Revenue from all entities you own or control >50%

This means: A company with $10M total revenue cannot create a $99k subsidiary to
avoid licensing fees. The threshold applies to the entire legal and economic
structure.

Example 1 (allowed): A non-profit with $50k annual revenue runs SENTINEL on their
platform. Compliant.

Example 2 (requires license): A company with $150k annual revenue deploys
SENTINEL. Must purchase commercial license.

Example 3 (not allowed): A company with $50M revenue creates a shell subsidiary
with $99k revenue to use SENTINEL. This is circumvention and constitutes license
violation.

---

HOSTED SERVICE RESTRICTION

You cannot run SENTINEL as a service for others without written permission. This
includes:
- SaaS offerings (Software as a Service)
- Managed hosting services
- API services that others use
- White-labeled implementations where customers do not control their own
  deployment

Exception: You MAY offer SENTINEL as an internal-only service to other
departments or entities within your organization, or to partners on a
non-commercial basis, if all parties are under your direct control.

---

ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT

If you use SENTINEL in production, you must:
- Retain all copyright notices in source code (do not remove or alter them)
- Display visible attribution to "SENTINEL by Sentinel Foundation" in any
  documentation, dashboard, About page, or public-facing materials that describe
  your safety systems
- Provide this attribution to end users or customers if they ask about your
  moderation technology

Attribution does not require linking to our website, but must be visible and
accurate.

---

ANTI-CIRCUMVENTION

Do not attempt to:
- Rename, rebrand, or fork SENTINEL to avoid these terms
- Create modified versions and claim they are new products with new rights
- Use SENTINEL as a component in a larger platform designed to circumvent the
  revenue threshold
- Transfer operations to a different legal entity to reset the revenue clock
- Use shell companies, trusts, or complex ownership structures to hide actual
  revenue

If you believe our interpretation of your situation is incorrect, contact us
before deployment. If you violate this clause knowingly, you forfeit all rights
under this license and must cease using SENTINEL immediately.

---

AUDIT AND VERIFICATION

Sentinel Foundation reserves the right to:
- Request reasonable written confirmation of your annual revenue if you claim
  status below the $100,000 threshold
- Ask for documentation showing your revenue calculation and entity structure
- Conduct reasonable compliance reviews to verify you are using SENTINEL
  according to these terms

If you fail to provide requested information within 30 days of a reasonable
written request, or if you provide false information, you are in material breach
of this license.

